<ab><lb n="1"/>  <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/><unclear reason="damage">ΙΙ</unclear>ΟΣ<gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/><unclear reason="damage">Ι</unclear>ΚΟΥ <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> ΤΕ<gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  <lb n="4"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/><unclear reason="damage">Ε</unclear> <w lemma="οὐδείς">οὐδεὶς</w> ΚΑ<gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  <lb n="5"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  <w lemma="ὁ"><supplied reason="lost">τῆ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ς</unclear></w>  <w lemma="ἐπιγραφή">ἐπιγραφῆς</w><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  <lb n="6"/><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/><unclear reason="damage">Λ</unclear> <g ref="#arabesque"/> <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>  </ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Fragments from a funerary prohibition - see commentary.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary" n="none">
            <p>Line 2 is perhaps a name followed by τοῦ τέ [κνου but two names in a genealogy are also possible.</p>
            <p> In line 3 the first letter might also be gamma, xi or tau; how the following letters should be divided is uncertain, bu tcf 1549 (= MAMA 556b), l. 3, ἕτερος δὲ οὐδείς· καί . . .  ,and no-one else (shall be buried there), and.</p>
            <p>Line 4 might be from a version of the formula τῆς ἐπιγραφῆς ἀντίγραφον ἀπετέθη εἰς τὸ χρεοφυλάκιον - a copy of this inscription was deposited in the Property -archive.</p>
            <p>Line 6 should be from the date for the relevant entry in the Property -archive.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography" n="none">
            <p>Unpublished.</p>
